transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hey, how you doing?

Speaker 1: Very well, sir. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Listen, I want to cancel this subscription.

Speaker 1: I don't want you guys to take money from my account again.

Speaker 2: This will be the first and the last, please.

Speaker 1: I can take a look into your prescription and see what's going on.

Speaker 2: What's your zip code?

Speaker 1: 75034.

Speaker 2: What's your last name?

Speaker 1: Bangali, B-A-N-G-A-L-I-I.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Yes, I see you got an order refilled today.

Speaker 2: This is two orders in total that you've had with us.

Speaker 1: No, no, no, no.

Speaker 2: Cancel everything. Cancel that. I don't need it.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir. So give me one second.

Speaker 2: I wasn't even able to say anything,

Speaker 1: and you just started to yell and talk over me.

Speaker 2: No, I'm not yelling, please. Sorry about that.

Speaker 1: No worries. No worries.

Speaker 2: You're not even giving me an opportunity to say anything.

Speaker 1: I already heard you the first time.

Speaker 2: It's fully canceled out, sir.

Speaker 1: You won't be able to order it again, to keep in mind,

Speaker 2: because the prescription does get deleted.

Speaker 1: But you're all set.

Speaker 2: So you delete everything, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's deleted. You can't order again either.

Speaker 2: So you're all set.

Speaker 1: Okay. No problem. So nothing's going to come out of my account, right?

Speaker 2: Correct, because you can't order again, sir.

Speaker 1: All right. No problem, then. Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Okay. Bye-bye.
